49 Ma Virgilio n’avea lasciati scemi 50 di sé, Virgilio dolcissimo patre, 51 Virgilio a cui per mia salute die’mi;
52 né quantunque perdeo l’antica matre, 53 valse a le guance nette di rugiada, 54 che, lagrimando, non tornasser atre.

query.result:
55 “Dante, because Virgil is going away,
56 do not weep yet, do not weep anymore;
57 because weeping will be necessary to you for another sword.”

58 Almost an admiral who in stern and prow 59 comes to see the people who serve 60 for the other ships, and to do well encourages them;
61 on the left bank of the chariot, 62 when I turned to the sound of my name, 63 which of necessity is registered here,
64 I saw the woman who before appeared to me 65 veiled under the angelic feast, 66 direct her eyes toward me from over there by the river.

82 She was silent; and the angels sang
83 immediately ‘In you, Lord, I hoped’;
84 but beyond ‘my feet’ they did not pass.

